about.description:
An opinionated, forwards-looking Python template for 2021.
Generate elegant, ready-to-use Python projects that have excellent continuous integration and deployment (CI/CD).
Integrated with Dockerhub, Github Packages, Azure, Conda-Forge, and an array of linting, static analysis,
security testing, documentation, dependency management, and CI/CD tools, including a custom tool to keep all
duplicate project metadata sychronized to a single pyproject.toml. You only need to interact with your project via
git, tyrannosaurus, and Github releases – all other integrations kick off from there.
through those.
about.summary: Generate elegant, bleeding-edge, ready-to-use Python projects with seamless CI/CD, fit for 2021+.

name: tyrannosaurus
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "tyrannosaurus" %}
{% set version = "0.8.8" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/tyrannosaurus-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 86c31f8e05b9c584e08f5b427e2f31043e540383f474a8dfe530c9ec5d1d3f13

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  entry_points:
    - tyrannosaurus = tyrannosaurus.cli:cli
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip >=20
    - python >=3.8,<4.0
    - poetry >=1.1.4,<2.0
  run:
    - grayskull >=0.8.4,<1
    - python >=3.8,<4.0
    - requests >=2.24,<3
    - tomlkit >=0.7,<1
    - typer >=0.3,<1

test:
  imports:
    - tyrannosaurus
  commands:
    - pip check
    - tyrannosaurus --help
  requires:
    - pip >=20
    - poetry >=1.1.4,<2.0

about:
  home: https://github.com/dmyersturnbull/tyrannosaurus
  summary: Generate elegant, bleeding-edge, ready-to-use Python projects with seamless CI/CD, fit for 2021+.
  license_family: Apache
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  description: |
    An opinionated, forwards-looking Python template for 2021.  
    Generate elegant, ready-to-use Python projects that have excellent continuous integration and deployment (CI/CD).
    Integrated with Dockerhub, Github Packages, Azure, Conda-Forge, and an array of linting, static analysis,
    security testing, documentation, dependency management, and CI/CD tools, including a custom tool to keep all
    duplicate project metadata sychronized to a single pyproject.toml. You only need to interact with your project via
    git, tyrannosaurus, and Github releases – all other integrations kick off from there.
    through those.
  doc_url: https://tyrannosaurus.readthedocs.io/
  dev_url: https://github.com/dmyersturnbull/tyrannosaurus

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - dmyersturnbull
